Reasoning: The paper deals with learning a controllable representation for high-dimensional observations of dynamical systems, which is a problem that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The use of machine learning techniques to learn the representation suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The focus on control and planning suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics) sub-categories. The use of dynamical systems suggests that it could belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the use of high-dimensional observations suggests that it could also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category.
